1. Children, O Children know your Fathers, & the God of your Fathers, Know your parents, for that is the firſt Comandement with Promiſe, & you ſhal honor your ſelves in honoring them.Camerar. oper. ſubcis. Centur. 1. cap. 66. Its recorded of the Catanenſes, that they made a Stately Monument of kingly Magnificence, in, remembrance of two Sons, who took their Aged Parents upon their Backs and carried them through the Fire when their Fathers Houſe was al in a Flame. And of al the Birds, the Stork hath the Name for the good Bird, and why? but becauſe the younger of them do help
and bear up the Elder, their weak Parents;
